							Find the Right Attorney
					</h2>

									<p>Pedestrian accidents can happen anywhere drivers and walkers share space: crosswalks, intersections, sidewalks, parking lots, or even residential streets. Many occur because drivers fail to yield, run red lights, back up without checking blind spots, or drive too fast for conditions.</p><p>AccidentLogic looks for attorneys who understand traffic laws and local ordinances governing right-of-way and can prove when a driver’s inattention or recklessness caused a collision.</p>

